The paper deals with handwriting text recognition using deep learning neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of transfer learning is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) to improve performance on small datasets. The paper also discusses the use of connectionist temporal classification (CTC), which is a technique used in speech recognition (cs.IR) and handwriting recognition (cs.CV). Finally, the paper uses artificial neural networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
